There's some parts missing, but hopefully this gives a general idea of my digital workflow! I used Photoshop CC and a Cintiq 27QHD for the entire process. For more info, check out my FAQ - loish.net/faq! Hope you enjoy this video and thanks so much for watching!! Music credits:
I Don't See the Branches, I See the Leaves by Chris Zabriskie is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution license (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
Source: http://chriszabriskie.com/dtv/
Artist: http://chriszabriskie.com/

node.text:
Here's the sped-up process for one of my digital paintings from 2016! I sketched it on paper, then scanned it in and painted it in Photoshop CC using a Wacom Cintiq 27QHD. For more info on my process, check out my FAQ - loish.net/faq!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by loish on September 07, 2021. May be art of outdoors.

node.text:
Somewhere in the south of France, there’s a tiny little village called Pagès that consists of only a few houses and an ancient renault that looks like it hasn’t been used in decades. It was practically an old ruin, but we watched an old man climb into that car and drive away like it was nothing. It was a very French Moment. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text:
My latest patreon tutorial is about sculpting with color, which is a process I use for almost all of my art. I love working in this way because it’s fun, efficient, and allows me to go with the flow! The tutorial runs you through the process with 3 different variations, and has tips for avoiding muddy colors, working intuitively, and building up your color scheme gradually.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Get it through my patreon for just $5 and you’ll also get access to 13 other full-length tutorials, as well as process videos and a bunch of other resources. Link in bio! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#digitalpainting #paintingprocess #colorfulpainting #characterart #artprocess

node.text:
Mark your calendars for October 11th! That’s my birthday, and it’s also the launch date for my third artbook, The Style of Loish. I’ve been working on this book for almost a year now and I can’t wait to share it with you guys. It will be about how I developed my own style, and also feature tips and exercises for artists who are still searching for their own artistic voice.  It’ll be full of artwork and insights into my process, while inviting the reader to reflect on their own influences and artistic style. And of course there will be goodies like prints, signed copies, and fun stretch goals! 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I’ll announce more about the kickstarter as we get closer to the launch date, but for now, remember the date: 💜 October 11th! 💜
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
(I named a different date previously, so be sure to update it if you noted that one!)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#artbook #digitalart #artisticstyle #digitalpainting #paintingprocess
